# CLI Contract Rules

- Keep response shapes in `src/types/` stable for `projects`, `sessions`, and `messages`.
- Preserve source behavior:
  - `--source` accepts only `claude`, `codex`, or `cursor`. Omitting `--source` means all sources unless `MMR_DEFAULT_SOURCE` supplies a default.
  - `--source all` is not a valid value.
  - The read/query commands (`projects`, `sessions`, `messages`, `export`, `remember`) work without `--source`.
- `sessions` and `messages` accept optional `--project`, optional `--all`, and `messages` accepts optional `--session`.
  - When `--project` is given without `--source`, search all sources.
  - Without `--project` and without `--all`, auto-discover the cwd project by default.
  - If cwd auto-discovery fails, fall back to all items across all projects/sources.
  - If cwd auto-discovery succeeds but there are no matching records, return the empty result instead of falling back.
  - When `--session` is given without `--project`, bypass cwd auto-discovery and search all projects; if `--source` is also omitted, print a stderr hint suggesting `--source` to narrow the lookup.
- `export` accepts optional `--project`.
- `export` with no `--project` infers project from cwd: Codex = canonical path, Claude and Cursor = path with `/` → `-` and leading hyphen. Output is `ApiMessagesResponse` (same as `messages`). `--source` applies to export the same way (filters which source(s) are queried).
- `remember` sends session transcripts to the backend chosen by `--agent` (`gemini`, `codex`, or `cursor`). When `--agent` is omitted, `MMR_DEFAULT_REMEMBER_AGENT` applies if set; otherwise the default is `cursor` (`composer-2-fast` unless `--model` is set). Memory-agent calls use a two-part system prompt:
  - Base (always present): agent identity + input format only. Must not contain output-directing language.
  - Output instruction (replaceable): without `--instructions`, uses the default (Purpose, Output Format, Rules, Resume Instructions). With `--instructions`, the user's text fully replaces the default output instruction.
  - The user prompt is neutral ("Analyze the following AI coding session transcript(s).") — the system instruction has sole authority over output behavior.
  - `MMR_DEFAULT_REMEMBER_AGENT=cursor|codex|gemini` may supply the default `--agent` when the flag is omitted.
- Keep `messages` pagination semantics: page from newest window, then return chronological order.
- Each `ApiSession` and `ApiMessage` includes per-item `source` and `project_name` metadata.
- Do not color JSON output; only color human-facing errors on `stderr`.

## Example

```rust
// ✅ GOOD
let descending = chronological.into_iter().rev().collect::<Vec<_>>();
let mut paged = apply_pagination(descending, limit, offset);
paged.reverse();

// ❌ BAD: breaks chronological return contract
let paged = apply_pagination(chronological, limit, offset);
```
